  <title>Printing a photo</title>
 <section id="printingphoto">
 <title>To print a photo:</title>
  <p>
   Printing preferences can be accessed in any one of the following ways:
  </p>
  
  <list>
  <item><p>Select the photo using anyone of the selection modes
        and click <gui style="button">Print</gui> from the secondary toolbar.
  </p></item>
  <item><p>
  Hold <keyseq><key>Ctrl</key><key>P</key></keyseq> after a photo is opened for viewing.
  </p></item>
  <item><p>
  Click on the gear icon in the primary toolbar and manually select <gui style="menuitem">Print</gui>.
  </p></item>
  </list>
  <p>
  From the printing preferences window:
  </p>
   <steps>
   <item><p>
   Select the printer from the <gui style="tab">General</gui> tab if more than one are available.
   </p></item>
   <item><p>
   Click on the <gui style="tab">Image Settings</gui> tab and specify the position of the image either manually or by dragging it in the preview.
   </p></item>
   <item><p>
   On the same tab optionally specify the height and width from the size section or leave them as default for best fit.
   </p></item>
   <item><p>
   Select the <gui style="tab">Page Setup</gui> tab if a high quality paper is used. The corresponding settings for the paper size and orientation can be set here.
   </p></item>
   <item><p>
   Click <gui style="button">Print</gui>.
   </p></item>
  </steps>
 </section>
